@page
@model WebApplicationTest.Pages.AboutModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Sakura";
    ViewData["HideNavbar"] = true;
    ViewData["HideFooter"] = true;
}

<div class="sakura-learn-container">
    <div class="sakura-learn-header">
        <h1>桜の文化</h1>
        <h2>The Culture of Sakura</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="sakura-learn-content">
        <div class="sakura-card">
            <div class="sakura-card-icon">🌸</div>
            <h3>Historical Significance</h3>
            <p>Sakura have been celebrated in Japan for centuries, symbolizing the ephemeral nature of life in Buddhist tradition. The practice of hanami (flower viewing) dates back to the Nara period (710-794).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sakura-card">
            <div class="sakura-card-icon">🗓️</div>
            <h3>Seasonal Phenomenon</h3>
            <p>The cherry blossoms typically bloom in spring (March-April) with the exact timing varying by region. The "sakura front" moves northward with warming temperatures.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sakura-card">
            <div class="sakura-card-icon">🎨</div>
            <h3>Artistic Inspiration</h3>
            <p>Sakura appear throughout Japanese art, literature, and music. They represent both beauty and mortality, a concept known as mono no aware - the pathos of things.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sakura-back-home">
        <a href="/Home" class="btn btn-sakura">Back to Home</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .sakura-learn-container {
        max-width: 1200px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem;
        min-height: calc(100vh - 56px);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }
    body,html{
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        height:100%;
        width:100%;
    }
    .sakura-learn-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        padding: 1rem;
    }

        .sakura-learn-header h1 {
            font-size: 3.5rem;
            color: #d23369;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .sakura-learn-header h2 {
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            color: #5d5d5d;
            font-weight: 400;
        }

    .sakura-learn-content {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .sakura-card {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 2rem;
        box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

        .sakura-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
        }

    .sakura-card-icon {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .sakura-card h3 {
        color: #d23369;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .sakura-card p {
        color: #666;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .sakura-back-home {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: auto;
        padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .btn-sakura {
        background: #d23369;
        color: white;
        padding: 12px 30px;
        border-radius: 25px;
        text-decoration: none;
        display: inline-block;
        transition: all 0.3s;
    }

        .btn-sakura:hover {
            background: #b52a5a;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(210, 51, 105, 0.3);
        }

    @@media (max-width: 768px) {
        .sakura-learn-header h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
        }

        .sakura-learn-header h2 {
            font-size: 1.4rem;
        }
    }
</style>